On January 24, the eve of the Chinese New Year, Cheng Guang, a native of Tianmen in Hubei Province, drove himself back to Tianmen from Wuhan. He witnessed the whole process of "closing down the city" : First, the railway and highways were closed, then some county roads and even rural roads were closed, many people have evaded police checkpoints by driving on rural roads. Later, he was blocked on a bridge, the local government had to send a ferry to take people into the city, no one of the empty cars crowded a bridge.

His wife, on the other hand, remains in Wuhan. They spent their first New Year's Eve without each other, never knowing when they would see each other again. Cheng Guang said, "Fengcheng" before, he and his wife also joked that "should not" Fengcheng, did not expect to come true, they have become the center of the epidemic.

"But when disaster strikes, it's hard to believe it's a disaster, " he told CAIJING.

Tens of millions of ordinary people in Hubei Province, because of the sudden outbreak of the disease, life has been re-divided, the Spring Festival has been re-defined. Society is paying more for this epidemic, including family, human, health and economy. A person living in Wuhan said it was the first time she had cried during the Spring Festival. "Big New Year's, why to separate, why to fight? "

On January 26, Xiangyang announced that it would block traffic from entering and leaving the city from the early hours of the next day. It means that, in addition to the mountains and forests all over Shennongjia, Hubei urban areas have entered the "closed city" state. They are Wuhan, Ezhou, Cyprus, Zhijiang, Qianjiang, Huanggang, Red Cliff, Jingmen, Xianning, Jingmen, Xianning, Xianning, Xianning, Xianning, Xianning, Xianning, Xianning, Cyprus, Xianning, Xianning, Xianning, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Brazilian Republic, the Republic,.

Hubei is a typical provincial capital for the large city, Wuhan Resources Concentration, traffic radiation around the shape. There is an "8 + 1" urban circle around Wuhan, and while many people are shouting "Go Wuhan, " the other 17 cities and areas under Hubei's jurisdiction outside Wuhan need more attention and support from the outside world.

A doctor at the Huangshi five hospital told Caijing that he was on duty in the infection clinic and had not had goggles for a long time. He was sprayed with saliva on his face every time he took out a throat test paper. Later, he finally got a goggles, and now I'm rubbing it with alcohol every day.

A paramedic at Xishui County hospital in Huanggang said he had just had a CT scan of a family of three and had two positive lungs, aged 28 and 29, where he had no goggles and was in close contact with the patient.

CAIJING interviewed nearly 50 people in the 17 cities, including front-line medical staff, residents in quarantine, farmers in mountainous areas and suspected patients. On January 26, we published the first part of the epidemic area report, and on January 27, we presented the second part of the report.

It was a special battle against an epidemic that had an unpredictable beginning but perhaps an ending, not just in Hankou, where the outbreak began, but also in Wuhan and its surrounding areas, in Hubei and across the country. Whether they are people fleeing from Wuhan, feverish patients, medical staff on the run, or ordinary citizens, they are the children and families of others, and the fates of all are intertwined here.

Wuhan, AN UNPROTECTED HIGH RISK NURSE:

"craniotomy in progress. Told patient had lung infection. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Yao fell asleep from the operation

Zhang Yao is a nurse in the Department of Surgical Anesthesia. On January 23, the day before the "city closure" in Wuhan, she received a phone call from her boss, who asked her if you were the youngest party member in the department and would like to play a pioneering role. She did not hesitate to say yes.

After Zhang Yao told her parents that the hospital needed to work overtime, she hitchhiked back to Wuhan overnight. But she did not tell her parents that her hospital was listed as the counterpart of the designated hospital, and that she had already been recruited and deployed and might go to the designated hospital in the future.

Zhang Yao told Caijing that on January 26, a patient with cerebral hemorrhage was taken to the emergency operating room. Relatives said there was no history of contact in Wuhan and no fever, and requested immediate surgery. But during the operation, they were told that the patient's CT results showed a lung infection and that he was a highly suspected new coronary.

"The moment we heard the results, all six of us were silent, " Ms. Zhang said.

Because the family was not informed in advance, all of the surgical staff did not wear special masks and goggles, and is very easy to expose the source of infection is the craniotomy. "We are all aware that we may be at high risk of infection, but we have no choice but to continue the operation. "

On the way to intensive-care unit after the operation, the family informed the doctor that the patient had been home with a fever for two days. When she returned home that day, she burst into tears.

She felt aggrieved, afraid that she would become an incubation period of patients, infected to other medical staff and patients. She was also confused, "to protect doctors, isn't it also to protect everyone? Why do patients keep secrets from us? "

Zhang Yao said, why didn't everyone do a good job of protection? Because the hospital is not a designated hospital, and the material capital is already small. Everything that could be sent to the fever clinic, and all the protective clothing that the surgical anesthesiology department could have were left to the anesthesiologists, because they're the most dangerous people. But because it's a designated hospital-to-hospital, a lot of the medical needs are transferred to them. "resources are hard to use unless you have to, and a mask can last for days. "

Working conditions don't allow her to be isolated at home for 14 days. Because the hospital is short-staffed, and because she lives in a hospital-arranged dormitory, with more than roommates. When she called a hotel that advertised a free room for doctors, she was told it was five rooms, one night only.

The dormitory is five kilometers away from the hospital, and now she has to walk home for more than an hour every day, because she gets off work too late and the shuttle bus waits for no one.

After returning to Wuhan, Zhang Yao in the circle of friends released a lot of donations for help, the epidemic and other information, but the family blocked. Her Mother didn't know what she was going through in the hospital, but kept asking, "how's it going? " "Is Wuhan Okay Now? " Ms. Zhang saw rumors that "Wuhan medical staff are 100 percent infected. ". She was furious. "What would my mother think if she saw this? "

The Lunar New Year was a difficult time for the family of Wang Shuping, whose mother had been quarantined for three days at the COVID-19 hospital in Tianmen.

On January 24, Tianmen first announced that it had confirmed three COVID-19 patients, aged 39,45 and 65, who had lived, traveled or had contact history in Wuhan. The source also indicated that 10 close contacts were being tracked and placed under medical observation.

Wang Shuping's mother was one of the 10 people who had close contact with the coronavirus patients. Wang Shuping told Caijing magazine that her mother was a doctor in the village clinic of Liangxiang village, Yuekou town, a subordinate of Tianmen. Eleven days ago (about January 16) , a fever patient from Wuhan came back to the clinic to see a doctor. Her mother later confirmed that, she wore a mask when she came into contact with her patients, as if it were part of her profession.

January 22, people in Foreign Wang Shu Ping in a phone call with his mother, heard the mother some slight cough, 24, the mother woke up after a fever symptoms. "My grandfather immediately sent her to the Third Hospital, where she has been quarantined ever since. "

Wang Shu Ping's mother came to the hospital on the day of the news, she was treated for fever patients have been confirmed coronavirus infection.

Wang shu-ping to the mother of the original CT film to a Wuhan University School of Medicine Teacher Diagnosis, the other response, CT show "Ground Glass Shadow" , it is likely to have infection. "My mother told me that she was in the hospital, in a room with another patient, " Wang said. "So far, she has not been asked to do any tests other than the CT scan. "

It is gratifying that Wang Shuping's mother is now in good condition, the condition did not continue to deteriorate. "She's already offered $200 for a CT scan, but other costs haven't been mentioned. The hospital has room service, but doctors and nurses are harder to see. "

Wang Shuping said she forwarded her mother's first official message on Wechat on Dec. 31,2019: "unidentified pneumonia in Wuhan. ". But later the direction became "there is no obvious person-to-person transmission" , "can prevent and control" , Wang Shu Ping also lost attention to it, let alone to the information insensitive mother.

"What I'm most angry about now is that if I had announced it 10 days later (they were 20 days late, at the height of the Chinese New Year Rush) , my mother would have avoided seeing this patient! "

Wang shu-ping said that besides her mother, she hoped the media and the government would pay attention to doctors in other villages'clinics. Other cities in Wuhan have been neglected, and she is now worried about the rest of her family, the grandparents and cousins, all of whom had close contact with their mothers.

Xianning, mother and brother on the line:

"It's bad news to be afraid every time you answer the phone. "

Even if the national highway is closed, there are plenty of ways to get to the Xianning even if Xianning is bordered by Wuhan.

Until January 24, the number of confirmed cases of coronavirus in Xianning was zero. That day, the test paper arrived.

The next day, Xianning sent out two messages, reporting seven confirmed cases of coronavirus and 21 more. The local figure of 43 cases released in the early morning of January 26 was the fourth highest in Hubei Province after Wuhan, Huanggang and Xiaogan.

Liu's mother is a surgeon at the first people's Hospital in Xianning. On January 25, her mother was told that Xianning's First People's Hospital, which specializes in Febrile patients, would empty the hospital and transfer other patients to other hospitals in the city.

These days the hospital began intensive training of medical staff, while the establishment of isolation wards, the various departments of the shift, including surgery.

Liu Mulin, who is away from home, is worried about his mother. She told Caijing that her mother had told her that on January 23, a patient with a fever had been referred directly to surgery, but that the fever patient was supposed to go to a fever clinic. The surgical staff were not equipped with N95 and protective clothing, and they were wearing disposable surgical masks and were in contact with the patient, including her mother.

A nurse later developed a cough and a low-grade fever and is now under isolation in the hospital. "But all the other doctors and nurses should go home and go to work. "

"My mother said that the N95 is definitely going to the front line because of the lack of supplies, so they can just wear normal masks, " Liu told Caijing, "My mother also says that if you don't retire, you have to fight when you have to fight. She applied to the front line for SARS back then, and now she's in her 50s, and she still thinks it's a doctor's mission. "

"She's the kind of person who comes in and does things for other people, regardless of herself, and that's why I worry about her. I keep telling her not to go in there when you're old, and she says she'll go back if the hospital needs her. "

"But I just can't rest assured, if the hospital doesn't give you enough protection, you go straight back, isn't that to die? "

Liu said she is now very afraid to answer her mother's phone, and especially hope to receive her call, mixed feelings.

Liu and his mother rarely called before, because she was also very busy at work, perhaps mother and daughter only once a month to call. "The last few times I've had a phone call from her out of the blue, she's been telling me that she had some news from the hospital, or an announcement, or that the number of people who had been diagnosed had suddenly risen again, and every time I've been told it's a more serious situation, it's made me more worried. "

Liu has seen many requests for help on the Internet from nearby cities, but not from Xianning, and the hospital only started accepting patients with fever on a temporary basis yesterday, so it is likely that the hospital has not yet prepared supplies. "I was especially worried about what would happen next, about my mother, " she said.

Liu said her brother, also a doctor, was born in November. Brother said he now home dare not touch, dare not hold children, can only see a few.

On January 25, Liu was told by his family that the roads leading from Wuhan to Xianyang might be cut off by direct excavation to seal off the city more thoroughly.

Red Cliff resident Wei Hui watched the Spring Festival gala with his family. He did not dare to laugh when he saw some funny scenes in the sketch. "I secretly felt that it was wrong to laugh at this time, " he said

Wei Hui said that from the beginning to now, he felt that people all over the country, even in the province, paid little attention to the cities and counties around Wuhan. The county's resources certainly can not be compared with those of Wuhan, but the number of people working in Wuhan is particularly large, so he is particularly worried about the situation in the surrounding counties.

He marshaled his concerns about the current situation: 1. Rumors are rife, and a lot of terrible information is either true or false. 2, the residents weak sense of protection, drug stores alcohol mask out of stock. 3. Hospital resources are scarce and can not be diagnosed without kits, medical equipment, medical equipment, reagents, medicines, protective equipment, decontamination equipment, consumables (of which face masks are in great demand)4, so neither the suspected nor the confirmed cases have been made public.

Wei Hui, like many other people interviewed, hopes that reporters can verify more and release more true information. He saw a video of a patient going down on Wechat, "it will make us especially panic. "

Gong'an County, Jingzhou, can't help but fret:

"The phrase 'if you really care, bring supplies' really pissed me off. "

Gong'an County is Jingzhou's largest county, about an hour's drive from Jingzhou. Gong'an County is a historical Gu County, the three kingdoms period, because left General Liu Bei (known as Zuo Gong) Troops Youjiangkou (now the county seat) , take "left public security camp camp" meaning, renamed the Public Security. Because of the special nature of Gong'an County's name, there is no public security bar in the TIEBA, but to enter the "Gong'an County" in order to have the county's Tieba, has been ridiculed by netizens is the only county in the country without Tieba.

Chen's sister works at the county people's Hospital, Gong'an County's largest. According to a notice on the local wechat public account, including the county people's Hospital and the Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine, a total of 34 medical staff are on the front line of prevention, control and treatment.

As of January 25, four cases had been confirmed in Gong'an County and about 28 cases had been admitted to the People's Hospital, Caijing reported.

The authorities in Gong'an County are still trying to screen people returning from Wuhan, but the infection department has moved other patients (such as those with tuberculosis or other infectious diseases) to other departments because there are not enough beds, Chen said, doctors in other departments and 34 health care workers in charge of prevention and control are currently in dire need of medical supplies.

"Jingzhou is still short of supplies, not to mention the county hospitals down there, " she said, adding that only the infection and ICU staff had N95 masks. Many doctors have to buy their own masks online, but most do not ship until years later.

A suspected patient in the town of Nanping, which is part of Gong'an County, was called in by villagers. Police and doctors loaded the patient into a car and sent him to hospital. But video and photographs taken by villagers at the scene showed neither the police nor the patients wearing masks.

"I am worried that my family is not fully aware of the situation. At present, many factories in my hometown have issued notices to delay starting work, but someone still needs to be on duty. Today, my mother went to the factory to work for a day. Before entering the factory, someone will take the temperature, " she said.

From 4 pm on January 26, Gong'an County announced that it would impose a traffic ban on all motor vehicles in the Tawau embankment area. One doctor said he needed to walk two hours to get to the hospital.

Chen Yidan found that her family and friends in her hometown did not know much about the situation in Gong'an County and were not very concerned about it. She became even more worried. "I felt like I was the only one who was in a hurry outside and could not wait to go back to see what was going on. "

She called the hospital volunteers to find out about the hospital, but the volunteers said they did not know the situation, only to accept supplies, and then directly hung up the phone. She also reached out to a doctor at the hospital, who would not say much, only saying, "if you really care, bring the supplies. " Chen said she was upset.

Chen compiled a document called "the general situation of the epidemic in Gong'an County, Jingzhou, Hubei. " She put her knowledge of reliable information, photos and donation methods into the document and sent it to other people who want to know the situation. "I was so angry, I went back to filing. "

It's also her way of showing love and care.

Xiangyang, who bought 500 eggs:

"We are far behind the rest of the world in our epidemic prevention efforts. "

On the night of January 27, Xiangyang announced a traffic ban in the early hours of the next day. Liu Yifan, a citizen, saw from his circle of friends that the train station was already crowded at night. People are seizing the last few hours to leave Xiangyang.

Xiangyang is the second largest city in Hubei's GDP and an important transportation hub in the region, but Xiangyang was the last core city to be shut down. There were no confirmed cases until January 26.

Looking at the surrounding cities one after another "closed city" , Liu Yifan's view of Xiangyang is the latest city to receive official epidemic education (New Year's Eve) , is the latest "closed city" cities, the latest cases of the city. This led many people around her to believe that Xiangyang was safe, even people close to her shouted "hang in there, don't break the zero" and "Xiangyang is a place of great fortune, the safest place in the country" . She thought it was ridiculous.

Liu realized the seriousness of the outbreak earlier than anyone else around him, but he could do nothing but worry every day. She learned that a local listed company also held the annual meeting as scheduled, when Wuhan was not "closed" , Wuhan, Xiangyang Branch of the people in the annual meeting hot exchange. As at 24:00 on 26 January 2020,36 confirmed cases had been confirmed in Xiangyang.

On January 20, Liu Yifan called the municipal government health hotline and asked if quarantine measures had been taken. She called again on January 24 and still got a similar response.

"Xiangyang has 6.05 million permanent residents, but the government has not done much, " Liu told Caijing. A few days before the official "closure, " the government shut down some of the city's bus lines and closed down a few shopping malls, but in her view, control is far from enough. "The lines that stop and the malls that close are not the most crowded malls, " she said, adding that the government did not ban gatherings and that no community members registered home visits to Wuhan's population.

When one of her neighbors returned from Wuhan, he did not receive any inquiries or notice, but only made a report to his unit. Downstairs in her neighborhood, there were cars with license plates beginning with E A.

And her hometown, Rural Xiangyang, until 26, until the completion of the village partition, Wuhan has not yet completed the statistics of returnees. According to her understanding, the village teahouse entertainment places open as usual, most people do not wear masks, the village government posted a notice, but many people do not know where posted.

"I would like to be able to close down the city, " Liu said, adding that more efforts should be made to control the city, so that we can see the government's determination to control the epidemic. Liu said that if people around him can not be awakened by the numbers, they should at least "close down the city" and control it forcefully, to make them understand the severity of the outbreak.

She had a quarrel with her family about the dinner for 25 people, and they all laughed at it. She didn't show up for the last meal, bought 500 eggs herself and waited to eat them at home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The banner "welcome home for Chinese New Year" has not yet been taken down

The notice came at the same time as the road closure. Without warning, the roads in Tai Tong Wan village and Fengshan, Shijiazhuang were completely closed in a single afternoon. "almost no villagers know that the road is blocked. Only when they want to go to town do they find that they can not get out, " Pan told CAIJING.

The latest figures show that Huanggang is the city with the highest number of confirmed cases outside of Wuhan, with a high number of infections and a shortage of medical supplies, but the anxiety in Huanggang did not immediately seep into the townships below.

The space distance between city and village may not be far, but the psychological distance between people is very obvious. People in the village had only a vague idea of what was going on in Huanggang and Wuhan. It wasn't until the New Year's Eve, when news of a suspected infection spread from the neighboring village, that people finally realized the seriousness of the situation. By then, the roads were closed, the town was inaccessible, and masks and medicine were not available.

On January 25,2020, high-quality medical teams from all over the country went to Hubei Province for support; on January 26, medical staff tested negative for viral nucleic acid after treatment. But the good news is not encouraging for the people of Datang Bay.

"It may be useful for cities like Wuhan and Huanggang, but it may not be our next towns in the short term, " said Pan Shun, who said Datang Bay is home to more than 700,000 people in Luotian County, there is only one big hospital in Luotian County, and the township health centre is woefully inadequate.

Here, a dozen villages share a small shop, the only place where goods can be purchased after the road closure, but the shop has no medical supplies. "The people who live in the village are left-behind children and the elderly, most of whom have never used masks in their lives. "

The only way to save ourselves now is to stay indoors and wait for news. In a village with no telephone or Internet service, the people who can't get to town are almost cut off from the rest of the world.

"You never know when the road will be unsealed, and what's more confusing is that even with the antidote, you don't know when it will be your village's turn, " said the man, who has a habit of calling a specific remedy a cure, it made him feel better.

21

Huangshi, Guangzhou Returnee:

"Too bad there was so much meat and food in advance. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Doctor of Huangshi Sanjia Hospital, isolation clothes instead of protective clothing, treatment towel as a neck protector

The guangzhou-huangshi train leaves on January 22, but Huangshi resident Chen Xue has not yet decided whether to get on.

Earlier, wandering the streets of Guangzhou, he saw a line of drugstores lining up on the street. He also bought two packs of face masks. In the early morning, he tossed and turned until two o'clock, constantly checking the news. The spread of pneumonia made him want to refund his ticket.

The thought soon passed. He said he is a very homesick person, "so even if the most difficult, the situation has become very serious, I also want to go back to be with relatives, rather than a person in the new year outside. "

He grew up in Daye and later moved to Huangshi, a city he described as "dusty" . Compared with other cities, such as Shenzhen, where cars try to accommodate pedestrians, Huangshi's is unapologetic. "It's like nothing has changed in 10 years, " he said.

As a city that started with mineral resources, Huangshi was once the second largest city in Hubei Province after Wuhan in economic strength. But as resources dried up, so did Huangshi.

The train needs to change at Wuhan on the way. Chen noted that there did not seem to be as many people wearing masks in Wuhan as in Guangzhou, "as if it was not very serious. " When he arrived in Huangshi, his father picked him up without a mask, and there was no tension at all.

But his worst-case scenario soon emerged: at 10 a.m. on the 24th, as Wuhan was sealed off, so was Huangshi. First the city, then the town, then the county, then the village. Masks were scarce, and he had to take his family's temperature twice a day, washing his hands, opening windows, ventilating and mopping the floor.

Huangshi was the last city in Hubei to report a confirmed case until 23:38 on January 25, when the government announced 31 confirmed cases and one death at a time.

The general explanation is that it took some time for the provincial level to recognize Huangshi's ability to self-test, and then Huangshi reported the suspected cases at one time for the purpose of confirming the case, there was no underreporting or underreporting by Huangshi.

Under the influence of the epidemic, one of his relatives canceled the wedding of the fourth day of the Lunar New Year. Relatives hesitated for a long time, calling Chen's mother the night before the cancellation. "I think I heard him say that it was a pity that there were so many dishes and meat prepared in advance for the wedding, " Chen said.

22

Huangpi District, son of a hospital front-line Father:

"My father used to say never do the right thing, but this time he's on the front lines. "

The overnight transoceanic video was Jia's only chance to talk to his father. The father, a doctor in the respiratory department at Huangpi People's Hospital, is shown wearing multiple protective clothing, taking off his mask in the lounge and taking a few minutes to chat with his son.

"Don't worry, " his father kept telling him. But Jia Shu thought to himself, "how could I not be worried? "

He knows what's going on at Huangpi Central Hospital: Patients with fevers are panicking, they're crowding out the emergency room, which is extremely prone to cross infection.

Fathers and other health care workers had to be on the go, "too busy, too busy to reach for their phones. ". On the evening of New Year's Eve, my father went home for a simple meal and went on to the hospital.

Besides being tired, he was more afraid of his father being physically attacked by the patient or being torn from his protective clothing. Face Masks and protective clothing have been in short supply, and their safety is not well protected.

Looking at the father in the video, Jia Shu has mixed feelings. He never thought that his father, such an ordinary doctor (far less than academician Zhong Nanshan, such a national scholar, a great man) , would be pushed to the forefront of epidemic prevention work by the tide of times. He lamented the great tension between the Little Guy and the big time.

Before that, he didn't even have a great image of his father. Father is just "vulgar can not be vulgar again" the common people, and many parents, will teach him to make good money, mixed society, "never do the right thing.

This time his father was in the forefront, Jia did not ask his father why he did and said different, "I know he did not answer, this is probably a person's intuition. "
